\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. C. heterophyllus} Desf.,{\i  Fl. Atl. }{\b 1}: 411 (1798). Stems up to 100 cm, erect, much-branched. Leaves 5-20 mm, elliptical, pinnately veined, dark green and stellate-pubescent above, with the veins scarcely impressed, paler and tomentose beneath, with prominent veins. Petioles 1-2 mm. Cymes 1- to 5-flowered. Pedicels 15-45 mm. Sepals 5, conspicuously pubescent, with stellate hairs and few long, simple hairs. Flowers 5-6 cm in diameter, purplish-pink. Style filiform.{\i  S.E. Spain} ({\i near Cartagena}). Hs. ({\i N.W. Africa}.)
\par

