\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. C. parviflorus} Lam., {\i Encycl. Méth. Bot.}{\b  2}: 14 (1786). Stems up to 100 cm, somewhat spreading. Leaves 10-30 mm, ovate, 3-veined in the basal half, grey-tomentose, petiolate. Cymes 1- to 6-flowered, more or less symmetrical. Pedicels 5-10 mm. Sepals 5. Flowers 2-3 cm in diameter, pink. Style absent.{\i  Aegean region; S.E. Italy; Lampedusa.} Cr Gr It Si ?Tu.
\par

