\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. C. varius} Pourret,{\i  Mém. Acad. Toulouse}{\b  3}: 312 (1788) ({\i C. pouzolzii} Delile). Stems up to 50 cm, somewhat spreading. Leaves oblong, 3-veined, grey-tomentose, sessile. Cymes 2- to 8-flowered, unilateral. Sepals 5. Flowers c. 2 cm in diameter, white. Style filiform. {\i S. France} ({\i Gard, Aveyron, Ardèche}). Ga. ({\i N.W. Africa}.)
