\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. C. psilosepalus} Sweet, {\i Cistin.} t. 33 (1826) ({\i C. hirsutus} Lam. (1786), non Lam. (1778)). Stems up to 100 cm, somewhat spreading. Leaves 20-60 × 5-20 mm, ovate-oblong to linear-oblong, green, 3-veined at least in the basal half, more or less hairy, with long, simple and stellate hairs on both surfaces, sessile. Cymes 1- to 5-flowered, more or less symmetrical. Sepals 5, the outer ovate, cordate at base, hirsute and long-ciliate. Flowers 4-6 cm in diameter, white. Style very short. •{\i   Portugal, W. Spain; N.W. France} ({\i doubtfully native}). *Ga Hs Lu.
\par

